flowRoot.flowPara: Mechanism explanation VIDEO
Narration with graphs, illustrations section

At a minimum pledge of a tenth of a cent per other patron, you'll give $1 when a project has 1,000 other patrons (thus $1000 total that month for the project); at 5,000 patrons, you'll put in $5 ($25,000 total), 10,000 patrons at $10 each provides a monthly $100,000 for the project.
If you're wealthier or extra passionate, you can make larger pledges.
Of course, if you just donate $10 via a regular donate button, we don't get $100,000. For a typical free/libre/open project, a few odd donations add up to maybe several $hundred a month.
If a project is incredibly popular, maybe everyone else has already donated $99,990 dollars without you. It won't make much of a difference if you add your $10 (aside from you feeling good about it).
That's why plain donate buttons have not solved our problems. Most people don't accept the cost and hassle of donating when they know it won't really change anything anyway.
But wouldnt you feel different it you knew that everyone else would together match you 10,000 to 1?!
That's what happens with Snowdrift.coop.
It works because we make our donation contingent on others donating. This minimizes the risks and maximizes our collective impact!
